<blockquote>
  <p>A girl (Hannah Cormick) contemplates selling her soul on eBay. Instead, she puts her brain on the internet, deleting it the next morning, though all-too-aware that her innermost thoughts are now out there in cyberspace. A young man (Michael Ellis) addresses us directly.  He loves us; he hates us. Then his deepest thoughts are interrupted by his mobile phone.</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>The girl scrapes her feet and rolls the dice as she tells us of three deaths caused by computers. The man moves in synergy with computer writing and live music on an upstage video screen.  Clearly and cleanly, the seven talented creators of â€œCognition: Part 1â€ delineate â€œthe disquieting consequences for humanityâ€ of new technologies.  And the worst possibility of all?  A supercomputer might delete all memory of us.</p>
